abbr: Scanner Access Now Easy
wp: Scanner_Access_Now_Easy

SANE consists of backends and frontends.
-
A *backend* is a driver for a (supported) scanner and camara → hardware/device[devices] that implements the SANE interface.

A *frontend* is an application that uses the the backend to access the supported scanners and cameras.


{ Frontends for SANE

  There is `xscanimage` but apparently, XSane has more features and is easier to use.

  → http://www.sane-project.org/sane-frontends.html[This link] has more frontends.

}

sa:

  → Linux/scanner

  → Linux/fhs/etc/sane_d/index
  -
  → Linux/fhs/etc/sane_d/dll_conf
  -
  → Linux/fhs/etc/sane_d/net_conf is the net backend configuration file.


  `sane-find-scanner` finds → hardware/SCSI[SCSI] and → hardware/USB[USB] scanners.
